answers.body_markdown:
If the column contains values exactly like the ones you posted, then the `Nth` element is at the `2 * N - 1` position in the comma separated list.&lt;br/&gt;
So do this:

    SELECT tfcolumn 
    FROM tablename 
    WHERE substr(tfcolumn, 2 * 5 - 1, 1) = &#39;1&#39;
Replace 5 with the index that you search for.&lt;br/&gt;
See the [demo][1].&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Or remove all commas and get the `Nth` char:

    SELECT tfcolumn 
    FROM tablename 
    WHERE substr(replace(tfcolumn, &#39;,&#39;, &#39;&#39;), 5, 1) = &#39;1&#39;
See the [demo][2].&lt;br/&gt;


  [1]: https://www.db-fiddle.com/f/hWJJQpbvoGEE46D9hmMHWW/0
  [2]: https://www.db-fiddle.com/f/hWJJQpbvoGEE46D9hmMHWW/2

